# ExtoArts — Environment Setup Guide
# ====================================
# Your credentials are saved in value.json.
# Follow these steps to move them into Replit Secrets so they are never
# stored in source code.
#
# ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# STEP 1 — Open Replit Secrets
# ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# In the Replit sidebar, click the lock icon ("Secrets") or go to:
#   Tools → Secrets
#
# ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# STEP 2 — Add each secret
# ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# For every key listed in value.json, click "New Secret" and enter:
#   Key:   (the JSON key, e.g.  SUPABASE_URL)
#   Value: (the JSON value, e.g. https://bigopvwtprisrfhuayxs.supabase.co)
#
# Required secrets — all must be set for the site to work:
#
#   SUPABASE_URL          Your Supabase project REST URL
#   SUPABASE_KEY          Your Supabase service-role (secret) API key
#   DB_HOST               Supabase connection pooler hostname
#   DB_PORT               Usually 5432
#   DB_NAME               Usually postgres
#   DB_USER               Your Supabase DB user (postgres.<project-ref>)
#   DB_PASS               Your Supabase DB password
#   RESEND_API_KEY        Resend.com API key for transactional email
#   SESSION_SECRET        A long random string, e.g. run:
#                           php -r "echo bin2hex(random_bytes(32));"
#   TURNSTILE_SITE_KEY    Cloudflare Turnstile site key (for CAPTCHA)
#   TURNSTILE_SECRET_KEY  Cloudflare Turnstile secret key
#
# ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# STEP 3 — Verify
# ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# After setting all secrets, restart the workflow:
#   php -S 0.0.0.0:5000 router.php
#
# Then visit /login and attempt to sign in. If it works, the DB connection
# is reading secrets correctly from the environment.
#
# ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# STEP 4 — Remove value.json
# ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Once all secrets are confirmed working, delete value.json from the project.
# It contains real credentials and must NOT be committed to version control.
#
#   rm value.json
#
# The PHP code in includes/db.php and includes/email.php already reads from
# getenv() first, so Replit Secrets will be picked up automatically.
#
# ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# WHERE EACH SECRET IS USED
# ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
#   SUPABASE_URL / SUPABASE_KEY  →  includes/db.php   (all database queries)
#   DB_HOST / DB_PORT / DB_NAME / DB_USER / DB_PASS  →  includes/db.php (legacy health checks)
#   RESEND_API_KEY               →  includes/email.php (order/auth emails)
#   SESSION_SECRET               →  index.php / includes/auth.php
#   TURNSTILE_SITE_KEY           →  rendered in forms (public, sent to browser)
#   TURNSTILE_SECRET_KEY         →  includes/auth.php turnstile_verify()
#
# ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# WHERE TO GET CREDENTIALS IF LOST
# ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
#   Supabase:   https://supabase.com/dashboard → Settings → API
#   Resend:     https://resend.com/api-keys
#   Turnstile:  https://dash.cloudflare.com → Turnstile → your site
